## What I Am Still Thinking About

One thing I am genuinely unsure about: how do you handle risk assessments when your information is incomplete? In a perfect world you have full visibility into your systems, your data flows, and your third-party dependencies. In reality — especially in smaller healthcare organizations — you often do not.

Do you make your best estimate and document your assumptions? Do you delay the assessment until you have better data? I am not sure what the right answer is yet. I imagine this is something risk professionals navigate all the time in practice, and I am hoping it becomes clearer as the project moves forward.

